document:
Lucy is the first space mission to explore a diverse population of small bodies known as the Jupiter Trojan asteroids. These remnants of our early solar system are trapped on stable orbits associated with - but not close to - the giant planet Jupiter. Trojan asteroids orbit in two "swarms" that lead and follow Jupiter in its orbit around the Sun and are thought to be comparable in number to the objects in the main asteroid belt between the orbits of Mars and Jupiter.

Over its 12-year mission, Lucy will explore a record-breaking number of asteroids: it will fly by two (plus a newly discovered satellite) in the belt of asteroids that circle the Sun between the orbits of Mars and Jupiter, and then eight Trojans, which includes five asteroid targets and the satellites of three of those. Lucy also will fly by Earth three times to get a push from its gravity, making it the first spacecraft to return to the vicinity of Earth from the outer solar system.

Once upon a time, there was a special spaceship named Lucy. Lucy had a very important mission - she was going to visit some special rocks that were very far away in space. These rocks are like a big family, and they live near a huge planet called Jupiter. 

Jupiter is like the big brother in the family, and these rocks are his friends who follow him as he moves around the Sun. Lucy was going to visit these rocks one by one to learn more about them. She was going to fly by some rocks that circle the Sun near Mars and Jupiter, and then visit even more rocks that are friends of Jupiter.

But Lucy was very smart - she knew she needed a little help from Earth to travel so far. So, she flew by Earth three times to get a little push from Earth's gravity. Lucy was very brave as she traveled so far from home, and she was going to be the first spaceship to come back to Earth from so far away in space.

So, Lucy's adventure is all about exploring and learning about these special rocks and showing us how amazing and big our solar system is. Just like how we learn new things every day, Lucy is also on a big learning adventure in space.
expand_doc:
"Lucy Spacecraft Successfully Completes Historic Mission to Explore Asteroids Near Jupiter

The Lucy spacecraft, aptly named after the famous fossil that shed light on human evolution, has made history by becoming the first spacecraft to visit a group of asteroids near the giant planet Jupiter. These asteroids, collectively known as the Trojans, are a fascinating group of space rocks that have intrigued scientists for decades.

Launched by NASA, Lucy's mission was to study these Trojans, which are believed to be remnants from the early days of our solar system. By analyzing these asteroids, scientists hope to gain valuable insights into the formation and evolution of our cosmic neighborhood.

During its journey, Lucy made strategic flybys of Earth three times to harness the planet's gravity and slingshot itself towards the distant Trojans. This innovative maneuver allowed Lucy to conserve fuel and reach its destination efficiently, showcasing the spacecraft's advanced navigation capabilities.

As Lucy continues its exploration, it serves as a testament to human curiosity and ingenuity, pushing the boundaries of space exploration and expanding our understanding of the vast universe we inhabit. The data collected by Lucy promises to unveil new discoveries about the origins of our solar system and the dynamic interactions that shape celestial bodies.

The success of Lucy's mission underscores the collaborative efforts of scientists, engineers, and space enthusiasts worldwide, highlighting the endless possibilities that lie beyond Earth's atmosphere. With Lucy paving the way, future missions are poised to unravel more cosmic mysteries and inspire generations to come."

Arnold Schwarzenegger

Governor of California from 2003 to 2011

Significant Facts

Born: July 30, 1947 in Thal, Austria

Married: Maria Shriver on April 26, 1986 (The couple filed for divorce in 2011.)

Political Party: Republican

Arnold Schwarzenegger was born in Thal, Austria, a small village bordering the Styrian capital of Graz. He immigrated to the United States in 1968 and became a U.S. citizen in 1983.

Schwarzenegger earned a BA in Business and International Economics at the University of Wisconsin-Superior. He received an honorary Doctorate from the University of Wisconsin-Superior in 1996 and an honorary Doctorate from Chapman University in 2002.
    
An increasingly politically active Republican during the 1990s, Schwarzenegger ran for the California governorship and won when Gray Davis was recalled in 2003. Schwarzenegger was sworn in as the 38th Governor of California on November 17, 2003, following careers in body building, business and entertainment. Schwarzenegger was the first foreign-born governor of California since Irish-born Governor John G. Downey (Governor of California from 1860 to 1862). While governor, Schwarzenegger focused on reducing California's greenhouse gas emissions, increasing the minimum wage, and updating the workers' compensation system. He was also a proponent of physical education and after-school programs, and supported the After-School Education & Safety Act, which passed in 2002.

**Headline:** Arnold Schwarzenegger: From Immigrant to California Governor, A Story of Leadership and Impact

**Subheadline:** A Look Back at the Remarkable Journey of Arnold Schwarzenegger

Arnold Schwarzenegger, a native of Thal, made a remarkable journey from a small village near a big city to becoming the Governor of California. Arriving in the United States as a young man, Schwarzenegger immersed himself in studies focusing on business and economics at a prestigious institution.

Throughout his tenure as Governor of California, Arnold Schwarzenegger made significant strides in environmental conservation and community development. Recognized for his efforts in promoting clean air initiatives and advocating for after-school programs, Schwarzenegger's leadership was akin to that of a superhero in the eyes of many.

Hailing from a different country, Schwarzenegger's rise to prominence served as an inspiration, embodying the classic tale of a foreigner turning into a local hero. His dedication to improving the lives of Californians and his relentless pursuit of a better future for all residents solidified his legacy as a transformative leader.

Arnold Schwarzenegger's legacy continues to resonate as a testament to hard work, dedication, and the profound impact one individual can have in shaping a brighter tomorrow for an entire community.
